# pwebcam receiver config — copy to mac/.env and edit
# Changes take effect after: bash mac/restart.sh  (or python3 mac/receiver.py for manual runs)

# ── ADB device targeting ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required when more than one ADB device is connected (USB phone + TCP TV box, etc.).
# Use one of the two options below; leave both commented for single-device setups.

# Option A — pin to a specific serial (run `adb devices` to find yours):
#DEVICE=R5CR90XXXXXXX

# Option B — target by transport type (only when exactly one of that type is present):
#CONNECTION=usb      # any single USB device  (adb -d)
#CONNECTION=tcpip    # any single TCP device  (adb -e)

# ── Camera API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# true  → Camera2 API, port 8081 (hardware/software JPEG toggled in-app)
# false → Camera1 API, port 8080 (software JPEG, most compatible)
# Omit or leave blank to keep the default (true).
# Note: Camera2 is throttled on LIMITED HALs (e.g. Kirin 659 / Huawei FIG-LX1).
#PREFER_CAMERA2=true
